ing asymptotic expression based on a single\ntemperature- and wavelength-independent spectral index used by astronomers is\nnot appropriate to describe the dust MAC and thus the dust emission, and may\ninduce significant errors on the derived parameters such as the dust mass and\nthe dust physical and chemical properties. Instead, dust emission models should\nuse the dust MAC as a function of wavelength and temperature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Sep 2011 12:23:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-30"}
